"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-06-paris-2024-olympics-ofili-oborodudu-fail\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Favour Ofili failed to make it to the podium after finishing in sixth place in the women's 200m final.  The 21-year-old bowed to pressure in the race, failing to fulfil expectations.  Ofili will now concentrate on the women's 4x100m relay.  Team Nigeria also suffered another disappointment with Blessing Oborodudu losing to Japan's Nonoka Ozaki in the bronze medal bout.  Oborodudu lost the women's freestyle 68kg bout 3-0.  She won silver three years ago in Tokyo.  EPL: Supercomputer predicts title winners, teams to finish in top four  UCL: Dessers rescues draw for Rangers against Dynamo Kiev  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"